        [
          "Process Mining",
          "Higher Education",
          "Blended Learning",
          "728 first-year students",
          "1 Engineering Mobile Apps course",
          "LMS logs, e-Textbook, Learning Tools",
          "Trace-SRL Framework",
          "[Task Analysis, Goal Setting, Working on Task, Coordinating Learning Task Sequences, Evaluating]",
          "Authors defined that a session would consist of an whole day. \n\nThe labelling of the learning actions was not specifically focused on just counting of different actions on the LMS and, instead, mapped actions to specific learning actions, which would then be used to identify micro-level SRL processes. \n\nMicro-level processes were then associated to macro-level SRL behaviors. ",
          "First Order Markov Models",
          "-",
          "-",
          "Authors obtain a matrix with the probabilities of transitions between learning actions. This will be the input\n\n",
          "-",
          "The first part of the work is to use FOOM to identify common sequences of actions. Because of information provided by instructors, the matrix is generated considering a whole day as a session. ",
          "Quality of the trace data\n\nDefinition of learning sessions"
        ],
        [
          "Process Mining",
          "Higher Education",
          "Blended Learning",
          "728 first-year students",
          "1 Engineering Mobile Apps course",
          "LMS logs, e-Textbook, Learning Tools",
          "Trace-SRL Framework",
          "[Session Matrices from FOMM]",
          "Authors defined that a session would consist of an whole day. \n\nThe labelling of the learning actions was not specifically focused on just counting of different actions on the LMS and, instead, mapped actions to specific learning actions, which would then be used to identify micro-level SRL processes. \n\nMicro-level processes were then associated to macro-level SRL behaviors. ",
          "Expectation-Maximization",
          "Gap Statistic",
          "4",
          "Tactic 1: Reading wuth Quizz - Reading oriented with an additional emphasis on Quizzes → the main tactic based even on the way the course was designed.\n\nTactic 2: Assessment and Interaction - Opposite of the first, almost 0 Reading. Mostly used to participate in assessments and interact with peers and teachers. \n\nTactic 3: Short Login and Interact - The most frequent tactic of the course, with the shortest learning sessions → students login and check announcements.\n\nTactic 4: Focus on Quiz - Quiz related activities.",
          "Informing seems to be a relevant construct for all Learning Tactics that were identified.\n\nMost micro-level processes adopted by students were part of engagement and evaluation… with planning being considerably less frequent. \n\nLearning actions can be converted into learning processes. \n\nAdoption of SRL-focused approaches may bridge the gap of “context-specific models and assist in the creation of more universal models”. ",
          "The first part of the work is to use FOOM to identify common sequences of actions.\n\nAuthors obtain clusters and map the micro-SRL processes to the different sequences of actions. A MANOVA Test is conducted to show that all 5 micro-processes are statistically significant. ",
          "Quality of the trace data\n\nDefinition of learning sessions"
        ]
      ],
      "index": 5
    }
